==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Cast iron
<hw>Cast" i`ron</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <def>Highly carbonized iron, the
direct product of the blast furnace; -- used for making castings, and
for conversion into wrought iron and steel. It can not be welded or
forged, is brittle, and sometimes very hard. Besides carbon, it contains
sulphur, phosphorus, silica, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cast-iron</ent>⟦br⟧
